Once when she had three pups, one of them died. For two days and nights she gave herself up to try- ing to bring it to life-licking it, and turning it over and over, growling over it, and all but worrying it to awake it She paid no attention to the living two, gave them no milk, flung them away with her teeth, and would have killed them, had they been allowed to remain with her. She was as one possessed, and neither ate, nor drank, nor slept‚ was heavy and miserable with her milk, and in such a state of ex- citement that no one could remove the dead pup.
